# ⚠️ IMPORTANT: Environment Configuration

This file contains placeholder values for sensitive credentials.  
**DO NOT deploy with these placeholder values!**

## Required Changes Before Deployment

### 1. Database Credentials
```env
DB_PASSWORD=CHANGE_THIS_PASSWORD_IMMEDIATELY
```
→ Generate a strong password for your production database

### 2. Email Configuration
```env
MAIL_USERNAME=CHANGE_THIS_EMAIL@gmail.com
MAIL_PASSWORD=GENERATE_NEW_APP_PASSWORD
```
→ Create a new Gmail App Password at: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords

### 3. Domain Configuration
Replace all instances of `yourdomain.com` with your actual domain:
```env
APP_URL=https://yourdomain.com
SESSION_DOMAIN=.yourdomain.com
SANCTUM_STATEFUL_DOMAINS=yourdomain.com
CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://yourdomain.com
```

### 4. Secrets Generated
✅ APP_KEY - Already generated  
✅ JWT_SECRET - Already generated

## Security Notes

- Never commit `.env` file to version control
- Store production `.env` securely (use vault or encrypted storage)
- Rotate credentials regularly (every 90 days recommended)
- Use different credentials for staging and production

## Verification Checklist

Before deployment, verify:
- [ ] All placeholder values replaced
- [ ] Database connection works
- [ ] Email sending works
- [ ] HTTPS configured
- [ ] CORS allows your domain
- [ ] Session cookies are secure

